  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      There is a growing body of evidence exploring the role of curcumin as a radioprotector
      against radiation-induced injury in normal tissues as well as a radiosensitizer in tumor
      cells. The aim of this study is to determine the efficacy of oral nanocurcumin in prostate
      cancer patients undergoing radiotherapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
